      • writeTo

        public void writeTo(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
        Description copied from class: Response
        Write this response to the given response object. This method can be overridden to provide custom responses. By default this method writes this object to the stream as XML based on JAXB annotations and sets the encoding (UTF-8) and content type (text/xml) to appropriate values. These to parameters should be changed for the response if format is changed in the overriding method. Additionally this method sets the HTTP basic authentication header if the status is set Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED.
        Overrides:
        writeTo in class Response
        See Also:
        Response.setDefaultAuthenticationHeader(HttpServletResponse), Response.setStatus(core.tut.pori.http.Response.Status)
